# Business QA Project Rules

## Project Overview
RAG-powered intelligent Q&A assistant for business systems. Uses Spring AI ChatClient for all AI interactions.

## Tech Stack
- **Backend**: Java 21, Spring Boot 3.4.x, Spring AI 1.0.0, MyBatis-Plus 3.5.7, PostgreSQL + pgvector
- **Frontend**: Vue 3, TypeScript, Element Plus, Vite 6
- **AI**: Spring AI ChatClient (OpenAI-compatible endpoint pointing to DashScope), DashScope SDK for Embedding only

## Package Structure
- `com.zhuangjie.qa` — root package
- `com.zhuangjie.qa.config` — Spring configurations (incl. S3Config, StorageConfig)
- `com.zhuangjie.qa.common` — Result, PageResult
- `com.zhuangjie.qa.controller` — REST controllers (prefix: /api/)
- `com.zhuangjie.qa.chat` — Chat/conversation services
- `com.zhuangjie.qa.doc` — Document management services
- `com.zhuangjie.qa.file` — File infrastructure (S3 storage, Tika parsing, content type detection, text cleaning)
- `com.zhuangjie.qa.change` — Git change detection + AI suggestion
- `com.zhuangjie.qa.rag` — RAG infrastructure (Embedding, VectorStore)
- `com.zhuangjie.qa.db.entity` — MyBatis-Plus entities
- `com.zhuangjie.qa.db.mapper` — MyBatis-Plus mappers
- `com.zhuangjie.qa.db.service` — MyBatis-Plus service layer
- `com.zhuangjie.qa.pojo.req` — Request records
- `com.zhuangjie.qa.pojo.vo` — View objects

## Coding Conventions
- Use Java 21 features: record, sealed interface, pattern matching, text blocks
- Constructor injection via `@RequiredArgsConstructor`
- Request/Response objects use Java records
- All REST endpoints return `Result<T>` wrapper
- Paginated queries return `PageResult<T>`
- No company-internal information in code or comments (this project is open-source)
- GroupId: `com.zhuangjie`, never use `com.al.risk`

## AI Usage
- All LLM calls go through Spring AI `ChatClient` (stream for chat, call for analysis)
- Embedding uses DashScope SDK adapter `DashScopeEmbeddingModel` (text-embedding-v3, 1024 dimensions)
- Never import spring-ai-alibaba; DashScope uses OpenAI-compatible interface
- Vector store: PgVectorStore with HNSW index, cosine distance, 1024 dimensions, table `qa_vector`
- `spring.ai.openai.base-url` must NOT contain `/v1` suffix (Spring AI auto-appends it)
- ChatMemory conversation ID via `ChatMemory.CONVERSATION_ID` constant (not hardcoded string)
- Chat memory: `MessageWindowChatMemory` (InMemoryChatMemory was removed in Spring AI 1.0.0)

## Vectorization Pipeline
- `@EnableAsync` on `QaApplication` enables async vectorization
- Upload/create/update → `VectorSyncService.asyncVectorize()` (runs in async thread pool)
- `ChunkSplitter`: splits by Markdown headings, then by paragraph, max 1000 chars per chunk, min 50 chars
- `VectorService.vectorizeDocument()`: delete old vectors → split into chunks → embed → store in PgVectorStore
- `VectorStore.delete(Filter.Expression)` for filter-based deletion (not `delete(String)`)
- `VectorService.search()` uses `FilterExpressionBuilder.in("module_id", ...)` for module-scoped retrieval
- 0 chunk edge case: if chunk count is 0, `vectorized` stays false

## Frontend Conventions
- Composition API with `<script setup lang="ts">`
- API layer in `src/api/index.ts` — axios with response interceptor unwrapping `Result.data`
- SSE streaming via `fetch` + `ReadableStream` (not EventSource)
- Time formatting via `utils/format.ts`
- Vite proxy: `/api -> http://localhost:8091`
- Element Plus locale: `zh-CN`, all UI text in Chinese

## File Storage
- MinIO (S3-compatible) for document file storage
- AWS SDK v2 S3Client with path-style access (`forcePathStyle=true`)
- Apache Tika for document parsing (PDF, Word, TXT, Markdown)
- Upload flow: validate → Tika detect type → Tika parse text → upload to MinIO → save metadata + parsed content to DB → async vectorize
- Config prefix: `qa.storage.*` (endpoint, access-key, secret-key, bucket, region)
- Bucket: `business-qa`, auto-created on startup

## Database
- PostgreSQL with pgvector extension
- Database name: `business_qa`
- Tables prefixed with `t_`
- Vector table: `qa_vector` (auto-created by PgVectorStore, HNSW index, 1024 dimensions)

## Configuration Notes
- `application.yml` base-url: `https://dashscope.aliyuncs.com/compatible-mode` (no trailing `/v1`)
- `application-dev.yml` contains actual API key & GitLab PAT — gitignored
- `.vscode/launch.json` has `AI_DASHSCOPE_API_KEY` env var for IDE launch
- MinIO startup scripts in `scripts/` directory (ps1 + bat)
